<subSubSection id="C3616572FF92E478A8B55171453BFCBA" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BC436F9FF92E478A8B55171453BFCBA" blockId="50.[151,1437,726,2014]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="B90FEAEBFF92E478A8B55171404DFCD6" bold="true" box="[199,334,798,823]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named for Ivor Cutler (
<date id="FFC51039FF92E478AB43517142B6FCD6" box="[817,949,798,823]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" value="1923" valueMax="2006">1923–2006</date>
), Scottish recording artist, whose several entomologically themed compositions include one that begins, “I am a yellow fly.”
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
